==English==
===Intransitive verb===
'''to sally''' ('''sallying''', '''sallied''')

#To make a sudden attack on an enemy from a defended position.
Example: "The troops sallied in desperation."

#To set out on an excursion; venture (often followed by "forth.")
Example: “As she sallied forth from her boudoir, you would never have guessed how quickly she could strip for action.”
*William Manchester

#To venture off the beaten path
Example: "A sally into the wide world beyond his home" (like foray.)


== ==Noun== ==


#A sortie of troops from a besieged place against an enemy.
#A sudden rushing forth.
#An excursion or side trip
#witty statement or quip

 
